Poor digital communication can lead to misunderstandings and negative outcomes. For example, sending an email without a proper subject line or using informal language when communicating with a professor can create a bad impression or result in the message being ignored. In professional settings, clear and respectful communication is very important.
This situation can be avoided by following proper email etiquette, such as using a clear subject line, formal greetings, and a structured message. Maintaining professionalism in digital communication helps build a positive image and ensures effective interaction. This task helped me understand the importance of proper communication and responsible online behavior.
